1... g4! { There are many little mini-motifs visible in the position, the rook eyeing h1, possibilities of ...Ne2+, possible exploitations of the loose rook on d7, but the real key is seeing that White's queen makes them difficult due to her control of the key e2-square. } (1... Qb5? 2. Rd4 Rxd4 3. Bxd4 { [%cal Gc3d5] } 3... Nd5 4. Qb3 $18 { was the game continuation, when our most recent world championship contender was simply down two pawns. }) 2. Qg3 (2. Rd4 gxf3 (2... Qxd4 { This desperado also wins too, e.g. } 3. Bxd4 gxf3 4. Bxc3 fxg2) 3. Rxc4 Rxc4 $19) 2... Qf1+!! { The real magic here, making full use of the active placement of Black's remaining attacking forces! } 3. Rxf1 (3. Kxf1 Rh1#) 3... Ne2# *


