1. Kb3! { White already has some long term positional trumps in the two bishops and dominance of the d-file. Ulf first removes the king from the c-file, which stops any possible ...Nd4+ resources, and hints at either Bb5 or Kc4-b5. } (1. Bb5 Nd4+ (1... Ne7 2. Rd8+ Rxd8 3. Rxd8+ Bf8 4. Rb8 $18) 2. Kb1 (2. cxd4 cxd4+ 3. Kb3 dxe3 4. fxe3 Bf8) 2... Nf5 (2... Nxb5 3. Rd8+ (3. axb5 Rf8 4. Rd8 Rb7 5. R1d6) 3... Rxd8 4. Rxd8+ Bf8 5. axb5 $18 { [%cal Gf4f5,Gd8b8] }) 3. Rd8+ Rxd8 4. Rxd8+ Bf8 5. Bd2! (5. Rb8 Nxe3 6. fxe3 c4! { [%cal Gc5e3,Gf8c5] }) 5... Rb7) (1. Be2 Nd4+ 2. cxd4 cxd4+ 3. Kb3 dxe3 4. fxe3 { [%cal Gg7f8] } 4... Bf8 $10 { [%csl Ge2,Gf8][%cal Gf8c5] }) (1. Rd7? Nd4+ $10) 1... Bf8 2. Bb5! { [%cal Gb3c4,Gc4b5] } (2. Be2! $18) 2... Rcc7? (2... Ne7!) 3. Bxc6 Rxc6 4. Kc4 { [%cal Gc4b5] } 4... Be7 5. Rd7 Rcc7 6. Rxc7 Rxc7 7. Kb5 { [%csl Gb5,Rb6,Rg8][%cal Gd1d7] } 7... Rc8 8. Rd7! (8. Kxb6 { [%cal Gb6a5] } 8... Rb8+ { [%cal Gb8b2] } 9. Kxa5 Rxb2 { is also winning, but why allow Black any activity? }) 8... Kf8 9. Kxb6 Ke8 10. Rb7 Bd8+ 11. Kb5 { [%cal Ge3c5] } 11... c4 12. Bc5 $18 *


